    ## Position [#](#position)
    {: #position }

    Control the display position of your tip.  By defualt, tips are positioned above the the element you are tiping.  Positioning allows you to modify that with the these classes:

    {: style="margin-left: 20px" }
    * `tip--top`
    * `tip--right`
    * `tip--bottom`
    * `tip--left`

    [position](#){: class="has-tip" data-tip="(default positioning)" }  
    [position](#){: class="has-tip tip--top" data-tip="has-tip tip--top" }_: top_  
    [position](#){: class="has-tip tip--right" data-tip="has-tip tip--right" }_: right_  
    [position](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom" data-tip="has-tip tip-bottom" }_: bottom_  
    [position](#){: class="has-tip tip--left" data-tip="has-tip tip-left" }_: left_  

  =code_sample_static
    a.has-tip.tip--top href="#" data-tip="has-tip tip--top" TOP TIPS!

