    ## Anchors [#](#anchor)
    {: #anchor }

    Control the anchor point of your tip.  By defualt, tips are anchored to the center point of the element you are tiping. Anchoring allows you to modify that anchor point with these classes:

    {: style="margin-left: 20px" }
    * `tip--anchor-right`
    * `tip--anchor-left`

    As you might expect, anchor control only works and `top` and `bottom`.

    #### Top

    [anchor](#){: class="has-tip tip--anchor-left" data-tip="has-tip tip--anchor-left" }_: anchor left_  
    [anchor](#){: class="has-tip tip--anchor-right" data-tip="has-tip tip--anchor-right" }_: anchor right_  

    #### Bottom

    [anchor](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-left" data-tip="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-left" }_: anchor left_  
    [anchor](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-right" data-tip="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-right" }_: anchor right_  

  =code_sample_static
    a.has-tip.tip--anchor-right href="#" data-tip="SO ANCHOR" anchored right

