    ## Flow [#](#flow)
    {: #flow }

    Control the way tips flow in your layout.  By default, tips flow evenly from the center.  Flow allows you to modify that with these classes:

    {: style="margin-left: 20px" }
    * `tip--flow-right`
    * `tip--flow-left`

    As you might expect, flow control only works and `top` and `bottom`.

    #### Top

    [flow](#){: class="has-tip tip--flow-left" data-tip="has-tip tip--flow-left" }_: flow left_  
    [flow](#){: class="has-tip tip--flow-right" data-tip="has-tip tip--flow-right" }_: flow right_  

    #### Bottom

    [flow](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--flow-left" data-tip="has-tip tip--bottom tip--flow-left" }_: flow left_  
    [flow](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--flow-right" data-tip="has-tip tip--bottom tip--flow-right" }_: flow right_  

  =code_sample_static
    a.has-tip.tip--flow-left href="#" data-tip="SUCH LEFT" lefty tip

